    • Constructor Detail

      • AutonDrive

        public AutonDrive​(GyroSwerveDrive swerveDrive,
                  double direction,
                  double distance,
                  double speed,
                  double wheelMarginOfError,
                  double correctionScalar,
                  FrameOfReference frameOfReference)
        Constructs an AutonDrive command.
        Parameters:
        swerveDrive - The GyroSwerveDrive drive train.
        direction - The direction, in degrees, to travel in. Zero degrees corresponds with directly forward, and an increase in direction corresponds with a direction further clockwise from a top-down view. This value must be on the interval [0, 360).
        distance - The distance to travel in the specified direction, in inches. This value must be on the interval (0, infinity).
        speed - The speed to travel at. This value must be on the interval (0, 1].
        wheelMarginOfError - The acceptable margin of error for each wheel, in degrees, away from their target steering directions before the robot starts actually moving.
        correctionScalar - The speed to turn at per degree offset from the intended direction. For example, if the robot is going ten degrees to the right of where it wants to, it will make a correction turn to the left at a speed of 10*correctionScalar. A recommended starting value is 0.01.
        frameOfReference - The FrameOfReference for this autonomous command.

      • fromMovement

        public static AutonDrive fromMovement​(GyroSwerveDrive swerveDrive,
                                      double inchesRight,
                                      double inchesForward,
                                      double speed,
                                      double wheelMarginOfError,
                                      double correctionScalar,
                                      FrameOfReference frameOfReference)
        Constructs an AutonDrive command from a desired distance to the right and forwards.
        Parameters:
        swerveDrive - The GyroSwerveDrive drive train.
        inchesRight - The number of inches to move to the right, where a negative value denotes movement to the left.
        inchesForward - The number of inches to move forwards, where a negative value denotes movement backwards.
        speed - The speed to travel at. This value must be on the interval (0, 1].
        wheelMarginOfError - The acceptable margin of error for each wheel, in degrees, away from their target steering directions before the robot starts actually moving.
        correctionScalar - The speed to turn at per degree offset from the intended direction. For example, if the robot is going ten degrees to the right of where it wants to, it will make a correction turn to the left at a speed of 10*correctionScalar. A recommended starting value is 0.01.
        frameOfReference - The FrameOfReference for this autonomous command. Note that a frame of reference relative to the field does not mean that inchesRight and inchesForward are relative to the initial position of the gyro: only steering is relative to the gyro's initial orientation.
        Returns:
        The AutonDrive
